name: World
description: Functions for getting and using world data, including blocks, entities, players, and environmental information. Accessible from scripts via the global `World` variable.

methods.name: isWorldLoaded
methods.description: Checks if a world is currently loaded.

methods.name: getLoadedPlayers
methods.description: Gets a list of player entities currently within render distance.
examples:
const nearbyPlayers = World.getLoadedPlayers();
Chat.log(`There are ${nearbyPlayers.size()} players in render distance.`);

methods.name: getPlayers
methods.description: Gets a list of all players currently on the tab list.

methods.name: getPlayerEntry
methods.description: Gets the tab list entry for the given player, or null if they are not on the list.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the player.

methods.name: getBlock
methods.description: Gets a helper for the block at the specified position (coordinates or Pos object). Returns null if the location is not loaded.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: The X coordinate of the block.

parameters.name: y
parameters.description: The Y coordinate of the block.

parameters.name: z
parameters.description: The Z coordinate of the block.

parameters.name: pos
parameters.description: Alternatively, a position object for the block.

methods.name: getChunk
methods.description: Gets a helper for the specified chunk, or null if it is not loaded.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: The X coordinate of the chunk (block coordinate >> 4).

parameters.name: z
parameters.description: The Z coordinate of the chunk (block coordinate >> 4).

methods.name: getWorldScanner
methods.description: Creates a WorldScanner or a WorldScannerBuilder to perform complex, filtered searches for blocks in the world.

parameters.name: blockFilter
parameters.description: Optional function to filter by block type.

parameters.name: stateFilter
parameters.description: Optional function to filter by block state properties.

methods.name: findBlocksMatching
methods.description: Finds the positions of all blocks matching a given set of IDs or filters within a specified chunk range.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: A single block ID or an array of block IDs.

parameters.name: chunkrange
parameters.description: The radius of chunks around the center to search.

parameters.name: centerX
parameters.description: Optional center chunk X.

parameters.name: centerZ
parameters.description: Optional center chunk Z.

methods.name: iterateSphere
methods.description: Iterates over every block within a spherical radius and executes a callback function for each one.

parameters.name: pos
parameters.description: The center of the sphere.

parameters.name: radius
parameters.description: The radius of the sphere in blocks.

parameters.name: callback
parameters.description: The function to call for each block found.

parameters.name: ignoreAir
parameters.description: Optional. If true, the callback will not be called for air blocks.

methods.name: iterateBox
methods.description: Iterates over every block within a box defined by two corner positions.

parameters.name: pos1
parameters.description: The first corner of the box.

parameters.name: pos2
parameters.description: The second corner of the box.

parameters.name: callback
parameters.description: The function to call for each block found.

parameters.name: ignoreAir
parameters.description: Optional. If true, the callback will not be called for air blocks.

methods.name: getScoreboards
methods.description: Gets a helper for accessing scoreboard data.

methods.name: getEntities
methods.description: Gets a list of entities in the world, with optional filters for distance, type, or custom logic.

parameters.name: (none)
parameters.description: Get all entities in render distance.

parameters.name: distance
parameters.description: Get entities within this distance from the player.

parameters.name: types
parameters.description: Get entities whose type ID is in this array.

parameters.name: filter
parameters.description: Get entities for which this function returns true.

methods.name: rayTraceBlock
methods.signature: rayTraceBlock(x1, y1, z1, x2, y2, z2, fluid)
methods.description: Performs a ray trace between two arbitrary points in the world to find a block.

parameters.name: x1, y1, z1
parameters.description: The starting coordinates.

parameters.name: x2, y2, z2
parameters.description: The ending coordinates.

parameters.name: fluid
parameters.description: Whether to include fluids in the trace.

methods.name: rayTraceEntity
methods.signature: rayTraceEntity(x1, y1, z1, x2, y2, z2)
methods.description: Performs a ray trace between two points to find the first entity intersected.

parameters.name: x1, y1, z1
parameters.description: The starting coordinates.

parameters.name: x2, y2, z2
parameters.description: The ending coordinates.

methods.name: getDimension
methods.description: Gets the identifier of the current dimension.
examples:
const dimension = World.getDimension();
Chat.log(`Current dimension: ${dimension}`); // e.g., "minecraft:the_nether"

methods.name: getBiome
methods.description: Gets the identifier of the player's current biome.
examples:
const biome = World.getBiome();
Chat.log(`Current biome: ${biome}`); // e.g., "minecraft:plains"

methods.name: getTime
methods.description: Gets the total number of ticks processed since the world was created. Returns -1 if no world is loaded.
examples:
const worldTime = World.getTime();
Chat.log(`Total world ticks: ${worldTime}`);

methods.name: getTimeOfDay
methods.description: Gets the current time of day in ticks (0-23999). Returns -1 if no world is loaded.

methods.name: isDay
methods.description: Checks if it is currently day time.

methods.name: isNight
methods.description: Checks if it is currently night time.

methods.name: isRaining
methods.description: Checks if it is currently raining.

methods.name: isThundering
methods.description: Checks if it is currently thundering.

methods.name: getWorldIdentifier
methods.description: Gets a unique identifier for the current world/server.
examples:
const id = World.getWorldIdentifier();
Chat.log(`World ID: ${id}`); // e.g., "127_0_0_1_25565" for a local server

methods.name: getRespawnPos
methods.description: Gets the player's current respawn position.

methods.name: getDifficulty
methods.description: Gets the current world difficulty as an integer (0: peaceful, 1: easy, 2: normal, 3: hard). Returns -1 if no world is loaded.
examples:
const difficulty = World.getDifficulty(); // 0: peaceful, 1: easy, 2: normal, 3: hard
Chat.log(`Difficulty level: ${difficulty}`);

methods.name: getMoonPhase
methods.description: Gets the current moon phase as an integer (0-7). Returns -1 if no world is loaded.
examples:
const phase = World.getMoonPhase(); // 0: full moon, 4: new moon
Chat.log(`Moon phase: ${phase}`);

methods.name: getSkyLight
methods.description: Gets the sky light level (0-15) at the specified position.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: X coordinate

parameters.name: y
parameters.description: Y coordinate

parameters.name: z
parameters.description: Z coordinate

methods.name: getBlockLight
methods.description: Gets the block light level (0-15) at the specified position.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: X coordinate

parameters.name: y
parameters.description: Y coordinate

parameters.name: z
parameters.description: Z coordinate

methods.name: playSoundFile
methods.description: Plays a sound from an external audio file relative to the script's folder.

parameters.name: file
parameters.description: The path to the sound file.

parameters.name: volume
parameters.description: The volume to play the sound at (0.0 to 1.0).

examples:
const clip = World.playSoundFile("notification.wav", 1.0);
// clip.stop();

methods.name: playSound
methods.signature: playSound(id, volume, pitch, x, y, z)
methods.description: Plays a built-in Minecraft sound.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The sound event ID.

parameters.name: volume
parameters.description: Optional volume.

parameters.name: pitch
parameters.description: Optional pitch.

parameters.name: x, y, z
parameters.description: Optional world coordinates. If missing, sound is played globally.

examples:
// Play a sound only to the player (UI sound)
World.playSound("minecraft:ui.button.click", 1.0, 1.0);

methods.name: getBossBars
methods.description: Gets a map of active boss bars.

methods.name: isChunkLoaded
methods.description: Checks if a specific chunk is loaded.

parameters.name: chunkX
parameters.description: The X coordinate of the chunk.

parameters.name: chunkZ
parameters.description: The Z coordinate of the chunk.

methods.name: getCurrentServerAddress
methods.description: Gets the address of the current server, or null if in singleplayer.

methods.name: getBiomeAt
methods.description: Gets the biome at a specific location, provided the chunk is loaded.

parameters.name: x
parameters.description: The X coordinate.

parameters.name: y
parameters.description: The Y coordinate (optional in some signatures).

parameters.name: z
parameters.description: The Z coordinate.

methods.name: getServerTPS
methods.description: Gets a formatted string containing various TPS measurements.
examples:
const tpsInfo = World.getServerTPS();
Chat.log(tpsInfo);

methods.name: getTabListHeader
methods.description: Gets the current tab list header.
examples:
const header = World.getTabListHeader();
if (header) Chat.log(`Header: ${header.getString()}`);

methods.name: getTabListFooter
methods.description: Gets the current tab list footer.
examples:
const footer = World.getTabListFooter();
if (footer) Chat.log(`Footer: ${footer.getString()}`);

methods.name: spawnParticle
methods.signature: spawnParticle(id, x, y, z, count, deltaX, deltaY, deltaZ, speed, force)
methods.description: Spawns particles in the world.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The particle ID.

parameters.name: x, y, z
parameters.description: The central position to spawn the particles.

parameters.name: count
parameters.description: The number of particles to spawn.

parameters.name: deltaX, deltaY, deltaZ
parameters.description: The random offset range for particle positions.

parameters.name: speed
parameters.description: The speed/velocity of the particles.

parameters.name: force
parameters.description: If true, particles will be visible from further away.

methods.name: getRaw
methods.description: Gets the raw Minecraft ClientWorld object.
examples:
const rawWorld = World.getRaw();
// Advanced, low-level interaction with the raw ClientWorld object

methods.name: getServerInstantTPS
methods.description: Gets the server's current instantaneous TPS.
examples:
const tps = World.getServerInstantTPS();
Chat.log(`Instant TPS: ${tps.toFixed(2)}`);

methods.name: getServer1MAverageTPS
methods.description: Gets the server's average TPS over the last minute.
examples:
const tps = World.getServer1MAverageTPS();
Chat.log(`1-Min Avg TPS: ${tps.toFixed(2)}`);

methods.name: getServer5MAverageTPS
methods.description: Gets the server's average TPS over the last 5 minutes.
examples:
const tps = World.getServer5MAverageTPS();
Chat.log(`5-Min Avg TPS: ${tps.toFixed(2)}`);

methods.name: getServer15MAverageTPS
methods.description: Gets the server's average TPS over the last 15 minutes.
examples:
const tps = World.getServer15MAverageTPS();
Chat.log(`15-Min Avg TPS: ${tps.toFixed(2)}`);
